  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to compare findings generated by CT-based autopsy (Virtopsy) with
      conventional autopsy and clinical diagnoses. Therefore all patients dying while receiving
      treatment in the Department of Intensive Care Medicine will be undergo virtopsy and, if
      relatives give informed consent conventional autopsy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to compare findings generated by computertomography-based autopsy
      (Virtopsy) with conventional autopsy and clinical diagnoses. Therefore all patients dying
      while receiving treatment in the Department of Intensive Care Medicine will be undergo
      virtopsy and, if relatives give informed consent conventional autopsy.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
